What is RabiesEcon in sentence: RabiesEcon is a spreadsheet - based tool ( S1 Appendix ) that incorporates a mathematical ( deterministic ) model of dog - dog and dog - human rabies transmission to estimate dog and human rabies cases averted , and the cost per human rabies death averted and per year of life gained ( YLG ) due to dog rabies vaccination programs .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We used RabiesEcon to estimate the cost - effectiveness of dog rabies vaccination programs in an illustrative East Africa human population of 1 million in a mixture of urban and rural settings .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: Because there are insufficient data from a single country in Africa for every input in RabiesEcon , we used data from a number of African countries , primarily Chad , Malawi and Tanzania ( Table 1 ) .
What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We built RabiesEcon to include a separate sub - model for each sub - region , urban and rural .
What is RabiesEcon in sentence: a Calculated using the RabiesEcon tool .
What is RabiesEcon in sentence: A user of RabiesEcon can alter almost all the input values .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We used a previously published model [7] as a basis for our mathematical model of rabies transmission incorporated into RabiesEcon ( for equations , see S2 Appendix ) .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We therefore , to make it easier to facilitate comparisons between no vaccination and dog vaccination programs , programmed into RabiesEcon a process to calculate a “ steady state ” of a near - constant number of annual cases of canine rabies in a “ no vaccination ” scenario .
What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We did this by programming RabiesEcon to run an initial 10,000 weeks ( S2 Appendix and Table 1 shows the specific parameters used ) .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: We note that deterministic models , of the type used to build RabiesEcon , allow for the number of infectious dogs to be reduced to less than 1 ( e.g. , 0.5 infectious dog ) , but still able to transmit .

What is RabiesEcon in sentence: And , users of RabiesEcon can easily ignore those “ pop - up ” outbreaks that occur in years well beyond the chosen analytic horizon ( e.g. , if the user runs a scenario in which dog rabies is eliminated by year 6 , “ pop up ” of cases in , say , year 16 can be assumed to be due to the mechanics of the model ) .
What is RabiesEcon in sentence: Note , that although we did not incorporate in this example the spaying of female dogs , such an option can be selected in RabiesEcon .
